<LENGTH>
<P>
148 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
O, YOSEMITE! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unhappily, Dolan's question "Who owns Yosemite?" may be answered before the 
contract renewal date in 1993. With the foregone conclusion of acquisition of 
MCA by the giant Matsushita Electric Industries Co. of Osaka, Japan, the 
control, as it now stands, of "the most scenic valley in the world," a national 
shrine and symbol of the beauty and majesty of our land, will no longer be in 
the hands of its rightful owners -- the people of America. 
</P>
<P>
RALPH FRYE 
</P>
<P>
San Bernardino 
</P>
<P>
Maura Dolan responds: Word of Matsushita Electric Industrial Co.'s interest in 
purchasing MCA Inc. did not surface until after the Los Angeles Times Magazine 
had gone to print with its Yosemite package. Since then, National Park Service 
director James Ridenour has told the chairman of MCA Inc. that the federal 
government would prefer to keep the Yosemite concession in American hands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
