<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My Darling Clementine (Channel 28 Sunday at 2 p.m.) is John Ford's memorable 
1946 take on the Gunfight at the O.K. Corral, starring Henry Fonda as Wyatt 
Earp and Victor Mature as Doc Holliday. 
</P>
<P>
Moonstruck (CBS Sunday at 9 p.m.): One of the juiciest romantic comedies of the 
'80s, this is the film that provided Cher the Oscar-winning role that let her 
comic sensibilities out for a romp as a young widow whose dull life suddenly 
shifts 180 degrees under the spell of an extraordinarily full moon. 
</P>
<P>
Featuring Nicolas Cage, Danny Aiello and Olympia Dukakis. 
</P>
<P>
Lady for a Day (AMC Thursday at noon) is the 1933 Frank Capra heart-tugger 
based on a Damon Runyon story about an apple peddler (May Robson) turned into a 
lady by a gangster (Warren William) to impress the daughter who never has known 
her; Capra remade it in 1961 with Bette Davis as "A Pocketful of Miracles." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Motion Picture Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
