<HEADLINE>
<P>
O, YOSEMITE! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I suppose it is unavoidable that the politics-for-profit element in Washington 
contaminates even our National Park Service, but I commend The Times and author 
Dolan for the enlightening article regarding Edward Hardy's and MCA's control 
over Yosemite National Park. It makes one wonder how the National Park Service 
could relinquish their responsibility for protecting the rights and resources 
of United States citizens to a portrait-oriented corporation such as MCA. 
</P>
<P>
Fortunately there are people and organizations such as Patricia Schifferle, Joe 
Boland, Dean Malley and the Yosemite Restoration Trust who will challenge MCA's 
self-serving agenda and force the responsible government agencies to live up to 
their responsibilities. 
</P>
<P>
CHARLES F. DOHERTY 
</P>
<P>
Hermosa Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
