CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
FOOD; 
</P>
<P>
HOLIDAY PUDDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A BLAZING Christmas plum pudding is as traditional in the British Isles as the 
Thanksgiving pumpkin pie is here. 
</P>
<P>
Gilliland's the Irish fondness for spiced-fruit mixtures, which originally 
included plums. Today, the pudding is a mellow melange of raisins, candied 
fruits, almonds, dark beer, honey and spices. 
</P>
<P>
Available now through the holiday season, the puddings sell for about $15 per 
pound and can be shipped anywhere in the country. 
</P>
<P>
Gilliland's Cafe, 2424 Main St., Santa Monica; (213) 392-3901. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
