</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BACH: "ITALIAN" CONCERTO; FRENCH SUITE NO. 5; FRENCH OVERTURE, BWV 831. 
</P>
<P>
Andras Schiff, piano. Omega OCD 1014. Schiff's Bach playing can seem 
two-dimensional to the Gould-touched listener. Here, Schiff subverts all detail 
to the melodic line, which he explores in a calm, singing style, always 
avoiding overstatement. Coloristic shadings and varied articulation, too, are 
eschewed. Yet these undemonstrative readings are engaging in their own way, as 
a study in Bach's flowing melodicism. TIMOTHY MANGAN 
</P>
