<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"CATHERINE CROZIER AT GRACE CATHEDRAL." Delos DE 3090 (compact disc). The 
veteran organist makes characteristically controlled, conservatively 
registered, musically persuasive cases for monuments of German Romanticism. 
</P>
<P>
Mendelssohn's Sonata No. 6, in D minor, and two of Schumann's B-A-C-H fugues 
benefit most from her deeply serious approach, while Liszt's Prelude and Fugue 
on B-A-C-H and Reubke's "94th Psalm" Sonata need an injection of fantasy and 
bravura dazzle as well as the astounding mechanical mastery. Delos captures the 
sound of the Aeolian-Skinner/Casavant instrument in the reverberant San 
Francisco cathedral with typical flair and fidelity. JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
