<TEXT>
<P>
So the British have to listen to new records on the radio instead of the ones 
they already own (Jeff Kaye, "It's Not Only Rock and Roll," Oct. 21). 
</P>
<P>
Maybe that's why young bands like the Pixies can develop big followings in 
Europe, while still being outsold by the Doors over here. 
</P>
