thirtysome- things who still like the radio but hate the new "bubble-gum" music 
-- just as their parents did 20 years ago. The British Radio Authority is 
right: We don't need to hear "Stairway to Heaven" on the radio anymore. We can 
hear it on elevators now. 
</P>
