<TEXT>
<P>
In response to Pete and Maria Francis' remarks about NC-17 and the number of 
times suggestive words appear in "Henry &amp; June" ads, I say that if they 
counted the times that words in movie ads -- and in the movies themselves -- 
pertain to violence, murder, mutilation and drugs, they would be appalled. 
</P>
<P>
Self-righteous people should lighten up and concentrate on the things that are 
destroying the world instead of berating movies or ads that contain (sexual) 
words and feature some nudity. 
</P>
<P>
I do not care if someone gets a little aroused from a movie that depicts sex, 
but I do care if someone tries to emulate Rambo or some crazed killer in a 
motion picture. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN BYRNES 
</P>
