<P>
BRITAIN TIGHTENS SEAT BELT LAW FOR RIDERS IN BACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain will make it compulsory for passengers in the back seats of cars to 
wear seat belts where these are installed, the government said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Junior Transport Minister Christopher Chope told Parliament the law, to become 
effective July 1, would save at least 100 lives and prevent 1,000 serious 
injuries every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
