<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ARCADIA; 
</P>
<P>
TEACHER CONTRACT APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Arcadia Unified School District board last week approved a new teachers' 
contract that includes a 5% pay raise for teachers. 
</P>
<P>
The one-year pact also includes a less expensive health plan and up to 40% 
higher stipends for coaches and other special personnel, bringing compensation 
levels close to the county average. 
</P>
<P>
First-year district teachers will now earn $31,832. 
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time the contract has been settled this early in recent 
memory. No outside negotiators were involved on either side," Supt. Terry 
Towner said. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement also satisfied Caroline Auburn, president of the Arcadia Teachers 
Union. "It was a great challenge for both sides to resolve this in a way that 
was amiable," she said. "Neither side felt like they had given away the shop." 
</P>
<P>
Teachers voted to ratify the contract Nov. 2. Negotiators had settled on a 
tentative agreement Oct. 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
