<P>
THE INIMITABLE JEEVES by P.G. Wodehouse (Penguin: $4.95) Typical pandemonium 
reigns when that regular chappie, unsuccessful arbiter of fashion and 
upper-class twit, Bertie Wooster, and his unflappably competent valet, Jeeves, 
are called to assist the scatterbrained Bingo Little in his pursuit of several 
delightfully improbable ladies, including Honoria Glossop and Charlotte Corday 
Rowbotham. Jeeves naturally saves the day, sorting out the myriad complications 
with his singular mixture of unfailing good sense, knowledge of human nature 
and inside information. "The Inimitable Jeeves" is one of four volumes of 
Wodehouse's popular comedy of manners that have been dramatized for 
"Masterpiece Theatre" on PBS. Charles Solomon 
