<P>
EMERGENCY POWERS LIFTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, South Africa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government lifted emergency powers in 13 black townships around 
Johannesburg on Friday, saying order had been restored to the troubled 
settlements after they were ravaged by black factional violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
