<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLOMBIA POLICE RAIDS DESTROY 17 DRUG LABS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police destroyed 17 cocaine-processing laboratories in a series of raids deep 
in the southeastern Colombian jungle, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Anti-narcotics police carried out the raids in a region known as San Jose de 
Guaviare and destroyed 17 drug laboratories and confiscated chemicals and 
equipment used to process cocaine, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
In the Caribbean port town of Cartagena, meanwhile, security forces seized 375 
pounds of pure cocaine that was being transported in an 18-wheel truck to a 
clandestine airport where it was destined for export to the United States, the 
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
