<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUTH C. JONES; RETIRED KINDERGARTEN TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ruth C. Jones, who taught kindergarten at Newhall Elementary School for about 
40 years, has died at a Valencia hospital. She was 86. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Jones died Wednesday of natural causes, according to a nephew. 
</P>
<P>
Born June 28, 1904, in Hibbing, Minn., she began teaching kindergarten at 
Newhall Elementary School in the early 1920s. Upon her retirement in 1962, the 
school declared a Ruth Jones Day and honored her with an open house, said Betty 
Granger, principal of Old Orchard Elementary School in Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
For several years after she left Newhall Elementary, she would return on the 
first day of school to greet the new kindergarten pupils. The walls of her room 
at the Santa Clarita Convalescent Hospital, where she most recently lived, at 
times were decorated with artwork done by schoolchildren. 
</P>
<P>
She has no immediate survivors. Her husband, Wallace Jones, died in 1964. 
</P>
<P>
Services are private. Eternal Valley Mortuary in Newhall is handling the 
arrangements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
