<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAY SEGAL SHAPIRO; COMMUNITY VOLUNTEER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A memorial service is planned Nov. 25 for Ray Segal Shapiro, community 
volunteer and wife of Rabbi Joshua Shapiro. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Shapiro died Oct. 20 at a Tarzana hospital of complications of heart and 
lung disease, said her husband. 
</P>
<P>
She was 87. 
</P>
<P>
Born May 14, 1903, in Romania, she came to the United States in 1921. 
</P>
<P>
She and her first husband, the late Morris Segal, owned liquor stores in Long 
Beach and Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
She moved into the Jewish Home for the Aging in Reseda in the late 1960s and in 
1976 married Shapiro, who was the home's rabbi for 21 years. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Shapiro was active in many organizations, including Hadassah, The Women's 
Zionist Organization of America; Workmen's Circle; American ORT Federation; 
United Jewish Appeal, and the United Way. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to her husband, she is survived by her son, Carol Segal of Los 
Angeles; sister Blanche Mason of New York City; eight grandchildren; and five 
great-grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
The memorial service is scheduled for 10:30 a.m. Nov. 25 at the Jewish Home for 
the Aging, 18855 Victory Blvd., Reseda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
