<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ELLIS, IRISH SHOOT DOWN IOWA, REACH SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LaPhonso Ellis sank five free throws in the final 86 seconds and Notre Dame 
held off Iowa, 77-68, Saturday night at South Bend, Ind., to advance to the 
semifinals of the Big Apple NIT. 
</P>
<P>
The victory sends Notre Dame (2-0) against third-ranked Arizona Wednesday night 
at Madison Square Garden in New York. 
</P>
<P>
Acie Earl's basket brought the Hawkeyes (1-1) to within 64-63 by sinking two 
free throws with 2:04 left, but the Irish made 9 of 14 free throws in the final 
1:26. 
</P>
<P>
Elmer Bennett scored 21 points and Ellis had 20 for the Irish. James Moses had 
11 for Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
Nevada Las Vegas 109, Soviet Union 80 -- Larry Johnson collected 38 points and 
20 rebounds and the top-ranked Rebels beat the Soviet National Team in an 
exhibition at Las Vegas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
