<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
LEUZINGER TOPS CRESPI, 20-16 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leuzinger High of Lawndale rallied to score 14 unanswered points in the second 
half for a 20-16 victory against Encino Crespi in a Southern Section Division 
III playoff game at Pierce College Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi (8-3), which had outscored its opponents, 93-22, in the second half 
before being shut out by the Olympians, led 10-0 in the first quarter and 16-7 
at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
But Leuzinger's secondary and its big-play offense overpowered the Celts in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
Leuzinger (8-3), the co-champion of the Bay League, will face Anaheim Esperanza 
in the quarterfinals Friday. 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 40, Buena 12 -- Quarterback Rob Johnson completed 16 of 19 passes for 
250 yards and three touchdowns to lead El Toro to a Southern Section Division 
II playoff victory at Buena. Johnson threw for two touchdowns early in the game 
and left with 11 minutes remaining. El Toro (10-1) will play Lynwood (6-5) in 
the quarterfinals Friday. Buena finished the season 5-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
