<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SAN CLEMENTE ISLAND; 
</P>
<P>
SAN PEDRO PILOT DIES IN PLANE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pilot working as a spotter for a commercial fishing boat died after his 
single-engine plane slammed into the center of the island, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert W. Bacon, 55, of San Pedro was flying solo when the Cessna 162 crashed 
on the island about 45 miles off the San Diego coast, U.S. Coast Guard Lt. Dan 
Mincher said. Bacon took off from Torrance Municipal Airport to find schools of 
fish for the San Diego-based vessel Santa Maria, Mincher said. When the pilot 
did not return, his business partner reported him missing. A Coast Guard Falcon 
jet HU-25A spotted the wreckage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
