<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MERCED; 
</P>
<P>
RECALL URGED OF JUDGE IN MOLESTATION CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A recall movement was started against a Merced County Superior Court judge 
because he allowed a convicted child molester to remain free pending an appeal 
of his case. 
</P>
<P>
Part-time high school teacher Ken Mackie said he is starting the recall against 
Judge Michael Hider to protect the children. If 10,000 signatures are 
collected, the recall will be placed on the ballot. A jury found Gary Parsons 
guilty Sept. 11 of molesting three boys. Hider sentenced him to 22 years, but 
ruled that Parsons could remain free in lieu of $300,000 bail, pending his 
appeal. Parsons failed to post the bail but has remained free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
